data.meta_description: Alex Chandon: Check out the list of all Alex Chandon movies along with photos, videos, biography and birthday. Also find latest Alex Chandon news on Times of India.
data.text:
Govt's UPSC 'lateral entry' U-turn: Coalition compulsion or opposition pressure?

timesofindia.com / Aug 20, 2024, 22:43 (IST)

The UPSC withdrew advertisements for 45 lateral entry jobs due to opposition from JD(U) and LJP regarding caste reservations. This decision underscores the coalition's influence on Modi's governance in his third term, marking a shift from his earlier terms where BJP held the majority.

India, Japan hold ‘2+2’: Here's what was discussed

tnn / Aug 20, 2024, 23:46 (IST)

India and Japan have agreed to enhance their defence-industrial collaboration, particularly focusing on the 'Unicorn' stealth antenna system for warships. They also aim to improve military interoperability through joint exercises and cooperation in space and cyber domains. The partnership is seen as crucial for maintaining peace and stability in the Indo-Pacific region.

Can Indian apparel exporters profit from Bangladesh turmoil?

the economic times / Aug 20, 2024, 10:53 (IST)

The recent political developments in Bangladesh, one of the world’s largest readymade garment hubs, have triggered a supply-chain rethink among global brands. What kind of opportunity will this create for Indian companies?

'We don't understand why ... ': 5 questions by SC in Kolkata doc rape-murder case

timesofindia.com / Aug 20, 2024, 14:27 (IST)

The Supreme Court criticised the Mamata Banerjee-led West Bengal government and police for their handling of the rape and murder of a trainee doctor at Kolkata's RG Kar College. It questioned various aspects, including the FIR, actions against the college principal, vandalism near the crime scene, the initial suicide angle, and delays in allowing the parents to see the body.

Troll patrol: Trump and Harris taunt each other in toxic campaign

tnn / Aug 20, 2024, 21:35 (IST)

Donald Trump intensified his efforts to undermine Kamala Harris by questioning her background and eligibility. He criticized her father's Marxist ties and accused Harris of socialist ideologies. These actions echo his past tactics against minority politicians, causing a rift among moderate Republicans and leading some to endorse Harris.

How Kolkata doctor’s rape-murder threatens Mamata’s grip on Bengal

timesofindia.com / Aug 19, 2024, 21:32 (IST)

As the Left discovered, there is a breaking point in politics when the tide turns. It turned 13 years ago against the communists. Is it starting to turn now against the TMC and Mamata Banerjee?

'Bringing OTT apps under telecom licence is violation of Constitution as ...'

timesofindia.com / Aug 20, 2024, 23:43 (IST)

Telecom operators like Airtel, Reliance Jio, and Vodafone-Idea pushed to bring messaging and video call apps under telecom licenses, citing their significant contribution to data traffic. The Broadband India Forum countered, calling it discriminatory and unconstitutional.
